{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"rosy-vigor-yoke","description":"## Why\nWith many attestations, every consumer must address a specific kind; today verify returns one verdict from one slot.\n## What\n`verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=...)` certifies a single kind; with no kind it returns a\n`{kind: verdict}` map over all present attestations. CLI: `--kind K` is the single-gate\nexit-code form (exit 0 iff certified); no `--kind` lists all kinds (exit 0 iff all certified).\nMCP + schemas updated. Back-compat: an old-style single signature reads as one kind.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/signing.py` (`verify_signature`, `verify_signature_cli`), `src/rebar/mcp_server.py`,\n`src/rebar/schemas/verify_signature_result.schema.json`.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=...)` returns one verdict; no-kind returns `{kind: verdict}`.\n- [ ] CLI `--kind K` exit 0 iff that kind certified; no `--kind` lists all, exit 0 iff all certified.\n- [ ] MCP tool + result schema(s) reflect the per-kind / map shapes.\n- [ ] Legacy single-signature ticket verifies under its derived kind.","id":"cc1b-3e3e-cd78-4d0b","parent_id":"4702-a55c-7aeb-445a","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Verification surface: per-kind verify + verify-all map"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782782698787140001,"uuid":"0dc8b2f9-42af-4b8f-9d0b-91594b166599"}